ANSWER-9
*Incremental Load
Because the dataset represents daily sales data, which changes every day and grows continuously.

*Justification:--
Daily sales data changes frequently
Only new transactions for the day need to be added.
Re‑loading the entire dataset every day is unnecessary and inefficient.

2️.Incremental load reduces processing time
Instead of loading all historical data again, the ETL pipeline loads only:
New records
Updated records (if any)
This saves time and system resources.

3️.Prevents duplication of historical data
A full load every day would repeatedly reload old sales records, causing:
Duplicate entries
Primary key conflicts
Data bloat

Incremental load avoids this.

4️.Standard industry practice
For transactional datasets like:
Sales
Orders
Payments
Inventory movements

Incremental loading is the standard ETL approach.

